This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) categories as it proposes a method to reduce the memory consumption of deep neural network training on image datasets. It may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category as deep learning is a subfield of AI. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of computation graph analysis, which is a technique commonly used in the neural networks (cs.NE) category. Finally, the paper discusses the optimization of memory usage during training, which is a topic relevant to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) category.
